data.title: Check Out The Punjabi Song 'Kangna' Sung By Biba Singh
data.meta_description: For all Punjabi music fans, check-out latest Punjabi song 'Kangna' sung by Biba Singh. The song is directed by Sandeep Sharma. Music of song 'Kangna' is given by Desi Crew and Bunty Bains, while the Lyrics of 'Kangna' song are written by Bunty Bains. To know more about the Biba Singh's song 'Kangna', enjoy the video. Stay tuned to ETimes for more songs like Kangna. Check out ETimes Punjabi music videos section for more Punjabi songs and Biba Singh songs.

Salman Khan Struggles To Stand At Ganpati Event; Video Leaves Fans Worried

Salman Khan made a stylish appearance at a Ganesh Chaturthi event, showcasing his signature dance moves to the tune of "Tera Hi Jalwa." However, a video captured him struggling to stand up from a couch, which quickly went viral. It was later revealed that Salman had suffered a rib injury. Despite the discomfort, he attended the event, and the wife of Maharashtra's Deputy CM was seen expressing her gratitude to him for his presence. Fans took to the internet to express their concern and wish him a speedy recovery. Salman Khan will next be seen in AR Murugadoss's film Sikandar.

682 views | 1 day ago

Salman Khan's Fan Touches His Feet; Actor's reaction Goes Viral

Salman Khan attended a Ganesh Chaturthi event in Mumbai, where various clips from the occasion have gained popularity online. Among these, a touching video of Salman’s interaction with a young fan is capturing widespread attention. The video shows Salman hugging the boy who had drawn a sketch of him. Moved by the gesture, Salman signed the sketch and was deeply touched when the boy touched his feet. In response, Salman lifted and hugged the boy affectionately. The video has gone viral, with fans praising Salman’s kind gesture. Salman will next be seen in AR Murugadoss’ film Sikandar.

3248 views | 1 day ago

Kangana Ranaut Criticises Sandeep Reddy Vanga’s 'Animal' for Promoting Violence; Sparks Debate

Kangana Ranaut recently condemned films that promote violence in society, criticizing the trend of patriarchal films that make a splash at the box office. In a recent interview, she specifically targeted Sandeep Reddy Vanga’s film Animal, expressing her disapproval of the portrayal of violence in such movies. She questioned the audience's enthusiasm for films that depict men engaging in brutal violence with no regard for law and order, highlighting the unrealistic depiction of crime in these films. Kangana’s upcoming film, Emergency, is set to release on September 6.

Hema Committee Report: Actress Sreelekha Mitra Accuses Malayalam Director Ranjith of S*xual Assault

In a shocking revelation, actress Sreelekha Mitra has accused renowned Malayalam director Ranjith of sexual assault, as reported by the Hema Committee. The allegations have sent shockwaves through the film industry, raising questions about power dynamics and the safety of women in cinema. This video dives deep into the details of the accusation, exploring the implications for Ranjith's career and the broader impact on the Malayalam film industry.
